<plot>A move back in time to once again gaze upon the noble face of our 16th president. The digital recreation of the face of Abraham Lincoln marks the first time an historic figure has been depicted with photographic accuracy. In a genre which lens itself to the creation of ugliness and monstrosities, this film shifts direction to the empathetic and loving portraiture of a fallen president.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?216729</url></doc>
